==English==

===Etymology===
[[Old English]] also adew, adewe, adue; French ''[[à]] [[dieu]]'', from Latin ''[[ad]]'', to + [[deus]], God.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈdjuː/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uː|-uː]]

===Interjection===
'''adieu'''

# Said to wish a fond farewell; good-bye.

====Synonyms====
*[[adios]], [[arrivederci]], [[auf wiedersehen]], [[au revoir]], [[bye]], [[bye-bye]], [[cheerio]], [[good-by]], [[goodby]], [[good-bye]], [[goodbye]], [[good day]], [[sayonara]], [[so long]]

